AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 593 House Bill No. 224*
by deleting § 49-2-903 in Section 1 and substituting:
49-2-903.
A local board of education may establish an investment trust for the purpose of
prospectively funding capital improvements for the benefit of the LEA. In order for a
local board of education to establish and maintain an investment trust pursuant to this
part, the local board of education shall:
(1) Adopt a capital improvements plan;
(2) Maintain a public school fund balance that is equal to no less than
two (2) months of expenditures based on the LEA's general purpose budget;
(3) Ensure that any transfer of funds to the trust are approved by the
local legislative body for the county or municipality that serves as the local
funding body for the LEA;
(4) Adopt, in writing, an investment policy that directs how assets in the
trust may be invested;
(5) Ensure that the trust conforms to all applicable laws, rules, and
regulations of the internal revenue service, if any;
(6) Ensure that the local board of education's capital improvements plan
is reviewed by a third party; and
(7) Ensure that the trust document is submitted to, and approved by, the
state funding board.
